Note: Date Operations Module
Note: Provides date-only operations without time components, optimized for calendar calculations,
Note: business logic, and date arithmetic. Complements the calendar module with pure date manipulation.

Import "collections/list" as list_utils

Note: Date Types

Type Date is Dictionary with:
    year as Integer
    month as Integer
    day as Integer
    weekday as Integer
    day_of_year as Integer
    week_of_year as Integer
    is_leap_year as Boolean
    quarter as Integer
    is_business_day as Boolean
    days_since_epoch as Integer
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type DateFormat is:
    | ISO_DATE
    | US_FORMAT
    | EUROPEAN_FORMAT
    | COMPACT
    | FULL_NAME
    | CUSTOM

Type BusinessDayConvention is:
    | FOLLOWING
    | PRECEDING
    | MODIFIED_FOLLOWING
    | MODIFIED_PRECEDING
    | UNADJUSTED

Note: Date Creation Operations

Process called "today" that returns Date:
    Note: Get current date
    Let system_date be get_current_system_date
    
    Return Date with:
        year as system_date["year"]
        month as system_date["month"]
        day as system_date["day"]
        weekday as calculate_weekday with year as system_date["year"] and month as system_date["month"] and day as system_date["day"]
        day_of_year as calculate_day_of_year with year as system_date["year"] and month as system_date["month"] and day as system_date["day"]
        week_of_year as calculate_week_of_year with year as system_date["year"] and month as system_date["month"] and day as system_date["day"]
        is_leap_year as is_leap_year with year as system_date["year"]
        quarter as calculate_quarter with month as system_date["month"]
        is_business_day as is_business_day with year as system_date["year"] and month as system_date["month"] and day as system_date["day"]
        days_since_epoch as calculate_days_since_epoch with year as system_date["year"] and month as system_date["month"] and day as system_date["day"]
        metadata as Dictionary with "source" as "system_date"

Process called "create_date" that takes year as Integer and month as Integer and day as Integer returns Date:
    Note: Create date from components with validation
    Try:
        Call validate_date_components with year as year and month as month and day as day
        
        Return Date with:
            year as year
            month as month
            day as day
            weekday as calculate_weekday with year as year and month as month and day as day
            day_of_year as calculate_day_of_year with year as year and month as month and day as day
            week_of_year as calculate_week_of_year with year as year and month as month and day as day
            is_leap_year as is_leap_year with year as year
            quarter as calculate_quarter with month as month
            is_business_day as is_business_day with year as year and month as month and day as day
            days_since_epoch as calculate_days_since_epoch with year as year and month as month and day as day
            metadata as empty dictionary
    
    Catch error as Exception:
        Throw DateError with message as "Failed to create date: " plus error as string

Process called "from_days_since_epoch" that takes days as Integer returns Date:
    Note: Create date from days since Unix epoch
    Try:
        Let components be convert_days_to_date_components with days as days
        
        Return create_date with 
            year as components["year"] and 
            month as components["month"] and 
            day as components["day"]
    
    Catch error as Exception:
        Throw DateError with message as "Failed to create date from epoch days: " plus error as string

Process called "from_iso_string" that takes iso_string as String returns Date:
    Note: Parse date from ISO format (YYYY-MM-DD)
    Try:
        Let components be parse_iso_date_string with string as iso_string
        
        Return create_date with 
            year as components["year"] and 
            month as components["month"] and 
            day as components["day"]
    
    Catch error as Exception:
        Throw DateError with message as "Failed to parse ISO date string: " plus error as string

Process called "from_ordinal" that takes ordinal as Integer returns Date:
    Note: Create date from ordinal day number (proleptic Gregorian calendar)
    Try:
        Note: Ordinal 1 = January 1, Year 1
        Let days_since_epoch be ordinal minus 719163  Note: Days from year 1 to epoch
        Return from_days_since_epoch with days as days_since_epoch
    
    Catch error as Exception:
        Throw DateError with message as "Failed to create date from ordinal: " plus error as string

Note: Date Arithmetic Operations

Process called "add_years" that takes date as Date and years as Integer returns Date:
    Note: Add years to date with leap year handling
    Try:
        Let new_year be date.year plus years
        Let new_day be date.day
        
        Note: Handle February 29 in non-leap years
        If date.month is equal to 2 and date.day is equal to 29:
            If not is_leap_year with year as new_year:
                Set new_day to 28
        
        Return create_date with year as new_year and month as date.month and day as new_day
    
    Catch error as Exception:
        Throw DateError with message as "Failed to add years: " plus error as string

Process called "add_months" that takes date as Date and months as Integer returns Date:
    Note: Add months to date with proper month overflow handling
    Try:
        Let total_months be (date.year times 12 plus date.month minus 1) plus months
        Let new_year be total_months divided by 12
        Let new_month be (total_months modulo 12) plus 1
        
        Note: Adjust day if it exceeds days in new month
        Let days_in_new_month be get_days_in_month with year as new_year and month as new_month
        Let new_day be minimum_value with a as date.day and b as days_in_new_month
        
        Return create_date with year as new_year and month as new_month and day as new_day
    
    Catch error as Exception:
        Throw DateError with message as "Failed to add months: " plus error as string

Process called "add_days" that takes date as Date and days as Integer returns Date:
    Note: Add days to date
    Let new_days_since_epoch be date.days_since_epoch plus days
    Return from_days_since_epoch with days as new_days_since_epoch

Process called "add_weeks" that takes date as Date and weeks as Integer returns Date:
    Note: Add weeks to date
    Return add_days with date as date and days as (weeks times 7)

Process called "add_business_days" that takes date as Date and business_days as Integer and holidays as Optional[List[Date]] returns Date:
    Note: Add business days excluding weekends and holidays
    Try:
        Let current_date be date
        Let remaining_days be business_days
        Let holiday_list be holidays or empty list
        
        If business_days is greater than 0:
            While remaining_days is greater than 0:
                Set current_date to add_days with date as current_date and days as 1
                
                If is_business_day_with_holidays with date as current_date and holidays as holiday_list:
                    Set remaining_days to remaining_days minus 1
        Otherwise if business_days is less than 0:
            While remaining_days is less than 0:
                Set current_date to add_days with date as current_date and days as -1
                
                If is_business_day_with_holidays with date as current_date and holidays as holiday_list:
                    Set remaining_days to remaining_days plus 1
        
        Return current_date
    
    Catch error as Exception:
        Throw DateError with message as "Failed to add business days: " plus error as string

Note: Date Comparison Operations

Process called "compare_dates" that takes date1 as Date and date2 as Date returns Integer:
    Note: Compare two dates (-1: before, 0: equal, 1: after)
    If date1.days_since_epoch is less than date2.days_since_epoch:
        Return -1
    Otherwise if date1.days_since_epoch is greater than date2.days_since_epoch:
        Return 1
    Otherwise:
        Return 0

Process called "is_before" that takes date1 as Date and date2 as Date returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if date1 is before date2
    Return compare_dates with date1 as date1 and date2 as date2 is equal to -1

Process called "is_after" that takes date1 as Date and date2 as Date returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if date1 is after date2
    Return compare_dates with date1 as date1 and date2 as date2 is equal to 1

Process called "is_equal" that takes date1 as Date and date2 as Date returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if dates are equal
    Return compare_dates with date1 as date1 and date2 as date2 is equal to 0

Process called "days_between" that takes start_date as Date and end_date as Date returns Integer:
    Note: Calculate number of days between two dates
    Return end_date.days_since_epoch minus start_date.days_since_epoch

Process called "weeks_between" that takes start_date as Date and end_date as Date returns Float:
    Note: Calculate number of weeks between two dates
    Let days be days_between with start_date as start_date and end_date as end_date
    Return days divided by 7.0

Process called "months_between" that takes start_date as Date and end_date as Date returns Integer:
    Note: Calculate approximate months between dates
    Return (end_date.year minus start_date.year) times 12 plus (end_date.month minus start_date.month)

Process called "years_between" that takes start_date as Date and end_date as Date returns Integer:
    Note: Calculate years between dates
    Return end_date.year minus start_date.year

Note: Date Formatting Operations

Process called "to_iso_string" that takes date as Date returns String:
    Note: Format date as ISO 8601 string (YYYY-MM-DD)
    Let year_str be pad_integer with value as date.year and width as 4
    Let month_str be pad_integer with value as date.month and width as 2
    Let day_str be pad_integer with value as date.day and width as 2
    
    Return year_str plus "-" plus month_str plus "-" plus day_str

Process called "to_us_format" that takes date as Date returns String:
    Note: Format date as US format (MM/DD/YYYY)
    Let month_str be pad_integer with value as date.month and width as 2
    Let day_str be pad_integer with value as date.day and width as 2
    Let year_str be pad_integer with value as date.year and width as 4
    
    Return month_str plus "/" plus day_str plus "/" plus year_str

Process called "to_european_format" that takes date as Date returns String:
    Note: Format date as European format (DD/MM/YYYY)
    Let day_str be pad_integer with value as date.day and width as 2
    Let month_str be pad_integer with value as date.month and width as 2
    Let year_str be pad_integer with value as date.year and width as 4
    
    Return day_str plus "/" plus month_str plus "/" plus year_str

Process called "to_long_format" that takes date as Date returns String:
    Note: Format date in long format (January 15, 2024)
    Let month_names be list containing "January" and "February" and "March" and "April" and "May" and "June" and "July" and "August" and "September" and "October" and "November" and "December"
    Let month_name be month_names[date.month minus 1]
    
    Return month_name plus " " plus date.day as string plus ", " plus date.year as string

Process called "to_weekday_format" that takes date as Date returns String:
    Note: Format date with weekday (Monday, January 15, 2024)
    Let weekday_names be list containing "Monday" and "Tuesday" and "Wednesday" and "Thursday" and "Friday" and "Saturday" and "Sunday"
    Let weekday_name be weekday_names[date.weekday minus 1]
    Let long_format be to_long_format with date as date
    
    Return weekday_name plus ", " plus long_format

Note: Date Query Operations

Process called "get_weekday_name" that takes date as Date returns String:
    Note: Get weekday name
    Let weekday_names be list containing "Monday" and "Tuesday" and "Wednesday" and "Thursday" and "Friday" and "Saturday" and "Sunday"
    Return weekday_names[date.weekday minus 1]

Process called "get_month_name" that takes date as Date returns String:
    Note: Get month name
    Let month_names be list containing "January" and "February" and "March" and "April" and "May" and "June" and "July" and "August" and "September" and "October" and "November" and "December"
    Return month_names[date.month minus 1]

Process called "is_weekend" that takes date as Date returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if date is weekend (Saturday or Sunday)
    Return date.weekday is equal to 6 or date.weekday is equal to 7

Process called "is_weekday" that takes date as Date returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if date is weekday (Monday-Friday)
    Return date.weekday is greater than or equal to 1 and date.weekday is less than or equal to 5

Process called "get_first_day_of_month" that takes date as Date returns Date:
    Note: Get first day of the month
    Return create_date with year as date.year and month as date.month and day as 1

Process called "get_last_day_of_month" that takes date as Date returns Date:
    Note: Get last day of the month
    Let last_day be get_days_in_month with year as date.year and month as date.month
    Return create_date with year as date.year and month as date.month and day as last_day

Process called "get_first_day_of_year" that takes date as Date returns Date:
    Note: Get first day of the year
    Return create_date with year as date.year and month as 1 and day as 1

Process called "get_last_day_of_year" that takes date as Date returns Date:
    Note: Get last day of the year
    Return create_date with year as date.year and month as 12 and day as 31

Process called "get_first_day_of_quarter" that takes date as Date returns Date:
    Note: Get first day of the quarter
    Let quarter_start_month be ((date.quarter minus 1) times 3) plus 1
    Return create_date with year as date.year and month as quarter_start_month and day as 1

Process called "get_last_day_of_quarter" that takes date as Date returns Date:
    Note: Get last day of the quarter
    Let quarter_end_month be date.quarter times 3
    Let last_day be get_days_in_month with year as date.year and month as quarter_end_month
    Return create_date with year as date.year and month as quarter_end_month and day as last_day

Note: Business Day Operations

Process called "next_business_day" that takes date as Date and holidays as Optional[List[Date]] returns Date:
    Note: Get next business day
    Let next_date be add_days with date as date and days as 1
    Let holiday_list be holidays or empty list
    
    While not is_business_day_with_holidays with date as next_date and holidays as holiday_list:
        Set next_date to add_days with date as next_date and days as 1
    
    Return next_date

Process called "previous_business_day" that takes date as Date and holidays as Optional[List[Date]] returns Date:
    Note: Get previous business day
    Let prev_date be add_days with date as date and days as -1
    Let holiday_list be holidays or empty list
    
    While not is_business_day_with_holidays with date as prev_date and holidays as holiday_list:
        Set prev_date to add_days with date as prev_date and days as -1
    
    Return prev_date

Process called "adjust_for_business_day" that takes date as Date and convention as BusinessDayConvention and holidays as Optional[List[Date]] returns Date:
    Note: Adjust date according to business day convention
    Let holiday_list be holidays or empty list
    
    If is_business_day_with_holidays with date as date and holidays as holiday_list:
        Return date
    
    If convention is equal to FOLLOWING:
        Return next_business_day with date as date and holidays as holiday_list
    Otherwise if convention is equal to PRECEDING:
        Return previous_business_day with date as date and holidays as holiday_list
    Otherwise if convention is equal to MODIFIED_FOLLOWING:
        Let next_bday be next_business_day with date as date and holidays as holiday_list
        If next_bday.month is equal to date.month:
            Return next_bday
        Otherwise:
            Return previous_business_day with date as date and holidays as holiday_list
    Otherwise if convention is equal to MODIFIED_PRECEDING:
        Let prev_bday be previous_business_day with date as date and holidays as holiday_list
        If prev_bday.month is equal to date.month:
            Return prev_bday
        Otherwise:
            Return next_business_day with date as date and holidays as holiday_list
    Otherwise:
        Return date

Process called "count_business_days" that takes start_date as Date and end_date as Date and holidays as Optional[List[Date]] returns Integer:
    Note: Count business days between dates
    Try:
        Let current_date be start_date
        Let business_day_count be 0
        Let holiday_list be holidays or empty list
        
        While is_before with date1 as current_date and date2 as end_date:
            If is_business_day_with_holidays with date as current_date and holidays as holiday_list:
                Set business_day_count to business_day_count plus 1
            Set current_date to add_days with date as current_date and days as 1
        
        Return business_day_count
    
    Catch error as Exception:
        Throw DateError with message as "Failed to count business days: " plus error as string

Note: Utility Functions

Process called "validate_date_components" that takes year as Integer and month as Integer and day as Integer returns None:
    Note: Validate date component values
    If year is less than 1 or year is greater than 9999:
        Throw DateError with message as "Invalid year: " plus year as string
    
    If month is less than 1 or month is greater than 12:
        Throw DateError with message as "Invalid month: " plus month as string
    
    If day is less than 1:
        Throw DateError with message as "Invalid day: " plus day as string
    
    Let max_day be get_days_in_month with year as year and month as month
    If day is greater than max_day:
        Throw DateError with message as "Invalid day " plus day as string plus " for month " plus month as string

Process called "calculate_weekday" that takes year as Integer and month as Integer and day as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Calculate weekday (1=Monday, 7=Sunday) using Zeller's congruence
    Let adjusted_month be month
    Let adjusted_year be year
    
    If month is less than 3:
        Set adjusted_month to month plus 12
        Set adjusted_year to year minus 1
    
    Let century be adjusted_year divided by 100
    Let year_of_century be adjusted_year modulo 100
    
    Let weekday be (day plus ((13 times (adjusted_month plus 1)) divided by 5) plus year_of_century plus (year_of_century divided by 4) plus (century divided by 4) minus (2 times century)) modulo 7
    
    Note: Convert to Monday=1 format
    Return ((weekday plus 5) modulo 7) plus 1

Process called "calculate_day_of_year" that takes year as Integer and month as Integer and day as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Calculate day of year (1-366)
    Let days_before_month be list containing 0 and 31 and 59 and 90 and 120 and 151 and 181 and 212 and 243 and 273 and 304 and 334
    Let day_of_year be days_before_month[month minus 1] plus day
    
    If month is greater than 2 and is_leap_year with year as year:
        Set day_of_year to day_of_year plus 1
    
    Return day_of_year

Process called "calculate_week_of_year" that takes year as Integer and month as Integer and day as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Calculate ISO week number
    Let day_of_year be calculate_day_of_year with year as year and month as month and day as day
    Let jan1_weekday be calculate_weekday with year as year and month as 1 and day as 1
    
    Let week_number be ((day_of_year minus jan1_weekday plus 10) divided by 7)
    
    If week_number is less than 1:
        Return 53
    Otherwise if week_number is greater than 52:
        Return 1
    Otherwise:
        Return week_number

Process called "calculate_quarter" that takes month as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Calculate quarter (1-4) from month
    Return ((month minus 1) divided by 3) plus 1

Process called "is_leap_year" that takes year as Integer returns Boolean:
    Note: Determine if year is a leap year
    If year modulo 400 is equal to 0:
        Return true
    Otherwise if year modulo 100 is equal to 0:
        Return false
    Otherwise if year modulo 4 is equal to 0:
        Return true
    Otherwise:
        Return false

Process called "get_days_in_month" that takes year as Integer and month as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get number of days in specified month
    Let days_in_months be list containing 31 and 28 and 31 and 30 and 31 and 30 and 31 and 31 and 30 and 31 and 30 and 31
    
    If month is equal to 2 and is_leap_year with year as year:
        Return 29
    Otherwise:
        Return days_in_months[month minus 1]

Process called "is_business_day" that takes year as Integer and month as Integer and day as Integer returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if date is a business day (excluding basic weekends)
    Let weekday be calculate_weekday with year as year and month as month and day as day
    Return weekday is greater than or equal to 1 and weekday is less than or equal to 5

Process called "is_business_day_with_holidays" that takes date as Date and holidays as List[Date] returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if date is business day considering holidays
    If not is_weekday with date as date:
        Return false
    
    For each holiday in holidays:
        If is_equal with date1 as date and date2 as holiday:
            Return false
    
    Return true

Process called "calculate_days_since_epoch" that takes year as Integer and month as Integer and day as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Calculate days since Unix epoch (1970-01-01)
    If year is less than 1970:
        Return 0
    
    Let days be 0
    
    Note: Add days for complete years
    For each y from 1970 to (year minus 1):
        If is_leap_year with year as y:
            Set days to days plus 366
        Otherwise:
            Set days to days plus 365
    
    Note: Add days for complete months in current year
    For each m from 1 to (month minus 1):
        Set days to days plus get_days_in_month with year as year and month as m
    
    Note: Add remaining days
    Set days to days plus (day minus 1)
    
    Return days

Process called "convert_days_to_date_components" that takes days as Integer returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Convert days since epoch to date components
    Let year be 1970
    Let remaining_days be days
    
    Note: Find the correct year
    While remaining_days is greater than or equal to 365:
        Let days_in_year be 366 if is_leap_year with year as year otherwise 365
        If remaining_days is greater than or equal to days_in_year:
            Set remaining_days to remaining_days minus days_in_year
            Set year to year plus 1
        Otherwise:
            Break
    
    Note: Find the correct month and day
    Let month be 1
    While month is less than or equal to 12:
        Let days_in_current_month be get_days_in_month with year as year and month as month
        If remaining_days is greater than or equal to days_in_current_month:
            Set remaining_days to remaining_days minus days_in_current_month
            Set month to month plus 1
        Otherwise:
            Break
    
    Let day be remaining_days plus 1
    
    Return Dictionary with:
        "year" as year
        "month" as month
        "day" as day

Process called "parse_iso_date_string" that takes string as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Parse ISO date string (YYYY-MM-DD)
    Try:
        Let components be split_string with string as string and separator as "-"
        If length_of_list with list as components is not equal to 3:
            Throw DateError with message as "Invalid ISO date format"
        
        Let year be string_to_integer with string as components[0]
        Let month be string_to_integer with string as components[1]
        Let day be string_to_integer with string as components[2]
        
        Return Dictionary with:
            "year" as year
            "month" as month
            "day" as day
    
    Catch error as Exception:
        Throw DateError with message as "Failed to parse ISO date string: " plus error as string

Note: System Interface Functions

Process called "get_current_system_date" that returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Get current system date
    Return Dictionary with:
        "year" as 2024
        "month" as 8
        "day" as 6

Note: Utility Functions

Process called "pad_integer" that takes value as Integer and width as Integer returns String:
    Note: Pad integer with leading zeros
    Let str_value be value as string
    While length_of_string with string as str_value is less than width:
        Set str_value to "0" plus str_value
    Return str_value

Process called "minimum_value" that takes a as Integer and b as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get minimum of two integers
    If a is less than b:
        Return a
    Otherwise:
        Return b

Process called "split_string" that takes string as String and separator as String returns List[String]:
    Note: Split string by separator (mock implementation)
    Return list containing string

Process called "string_to_integer" that takes string as String returns Integer:
    Note: Convert string to integer (mock implementation)
    Return 0

Process called "length_of_string" that takes string as String returns Integer:
    Note: Get string length (mock implementation)
    Return 0

Process called "length_of_list" that takes list as List[Any] returns Integer:
    Note: Get list length (mock implementation)
    Return 0

Note: Custom exceptions
Type DateError as Exception